28-year-old chef found dead in San Francisco mall
The 28-year-old chef, who recently moved to San Francisco, was found dead in the stairwell of a local mall this week.
However, the victim&#39;s brother says he can&#39;t imagine anyone willing to hurt him, remarking, &quot;Finally, things were looking up for him.&quot;
A body found at Westfield Mall on Wednesday morning has been identified as 28-year-old San Francisco resident Frank Galicia, the San Francisco Medical Examiner&#39;s Bureau said.
The San Francisco Police Department says the death has been classified as a homicide and the investigation is ongoing.
The victim&#39;s brother, Luis Galicia, told ABC&#39;s KGO channel in San Francisco that Frank, a former takeout line cook in Boston, landed his dream job as a cook at San Francisco&#39;s Sons &amp; Daughters restaurant six months ago.
A spokesman for Sons &amp; Daughters said they were &quot;shocked and devastated&quot; by his death.
&quot;We are a small team that works like a close-knit family and he will be greatly missed,&quot; the spokesman said.
Our thoughts and condolences to Frank&#39;s family and friends during this difficult time.
Luis Galicia said that Frank initially stayed in hostels, but lately, &quot;Finally, things were going well for him.&quot;
&quot;He found an apartment, he dated a girl,&quot; Luis Galicia told KGO.
Luis Galicia said he couldn&#39;t imagine anyone who would be willing to hurt his younger brother.
He had a kind soul and a big heart.
His way of connecting with his family has always been to prepare a meal for us, cook us dinner,&quot; said Luis Galicia.
He never wanted to be involved in any quarrel.
He was a brother who went with the flow.
&quot;For all the bad things that happen to this world, he was that rough diamond that shone bright every day,&quot; he said.
Anyone with information is asked to call the SFPD Hotline at 415-575-4444.
