However, the importance of exercise cannot be underestimated.
Those who exercise regularly reduce their chances of developing cancer or depression.
Physical activity helps with weight management, high blood pressure, diabetes and a long list of benefits too long to list here.
But the beauty of Pokémon Go is that it takes people outside to do what they love.
Thus, the three foundations of health are covered: movement, fresh air and sunshine and joy.
Some people even make new friends on the hunt.
As usual, there are boring bores who are looking for something to complain about.
And yes, someone might stumble on the door.
So what?
The breakthrough has happened.
Because even though smartphone apps like Fitbit could track our physical activity before, they didn&#39;t give us a reason to exercise like this game does.
The novelty will become boring, and the use will weaken over time.
However, due to the success of Pokemon, there will be more games that will combine apps and virtual reality with physical activity in the real world, helping many people on the hunt to be more active, fit and healthy.
