It is him that President Erdogan considers the organizer of the military coup attempt on July 15.
Fethullah Gulen lives in the United States, the Turkish authorities demand his extradition.
According to local media, a warrant for the arrest of Hakan Shukur was issued today, the police have already searched two houses that belong to the family of the former football player.
According to investigators, in addition to Hakan Shukur himself, Fethullah Gülen&#39;s organization also included his father.
However, neither the former footballer nor his relatives were there.
He and his family now live in the United States.
When he was a football player, Hakan Shukur defended the colors of several Turkish clubs and played for the national team.
He spent most of his career at Galatasaray.
The list of foreign clubs includes the Italian &quot;Torino&quot;, &quot;Inter&quot; and &quot;Palermo&quot;, as well as the English &quot;Blackburn&quot;.
True, he did not spend more than one season in any of them.
Hakan Şukur is still the most productive striker of the Turkish national team: he has 112 caps for the national team and 51 goals scored.
In 2013, Hakan Shukur left his deputy post due to the start of a corruption investigation around Erdogan&#39;s party and his inner circle.
