The Russian Copper Company (RCC) is ready to take on social responsibility and pay more attention to the environmental aspects of its business.
This is confirmed, for example, by the fact that the RCC has taken up the modernization of one of the oldest and environmentally &quot;dirty&quot; enterprises in the country - the Karabash copper smelter.
The Karabash copper smelter was founded by an English joint-stock company headed by Leslie Urquhart in 1910.
In Soviet times, it was a significant industrial enterprise for the country&#39;s economy, and it actually provided the life of the whole city.
However, in the 1990s, due to financial problems, production was stopped, which led to serious social problems in Karabash.
In 1998, a decision was made to resume the work of the Karabash copper smelter.
It was also necessary to solve one of the main problems of the Karabash plant - environmental.
By the early 2000s, Karabash was already infamous as an ecological disaster zone.
The situation at Karabashmed began to change in 2004, after the company was taken over by the Russian Copper Company.
The company began to modernize production, which began to gradually reduce the environmental impact on the environment.
This was recently noted by the governor of the Chelyabinsk region, Boris Dubrovsky, who visited Karabashmed in early July.
The head of the Southern Urals called grandiose changes that have taken place with the enterprise since Karabashmed was transferred to the RMK group.
The main event for the modernization of Karabashmedi in recent years has been the construction of a new sulfuric acid plant, which makes it possible to capture up to 99.9% of metallurgical gases.
According to the President of the Russian Copper Company Vsevolod Levin, the volume of investments in this project amounted to about 7 billion rubles.
The next stage of modernization of CJSC Karabashmed is the reconstruction of the converter section.
The replacement of three converters, dusters, gas duct is scheduled for the end of 2017.
The cost of the project is 2.5 billion rubles.
In addition, at the end of 2016, it is planned to launch a new industrial wastewater treatment plant worth RUB 1 billion.
In turn, the amount of taxes deducted to the budget of the city of Karabash will also increase.
For the entire period of implementation of the Tominsky GOK project - from the start of construction to the commissioning of the second stage - the federal treasury will receive 8.9 billion rubles.
And after the GOK is put into operation, tax revenues to the budgets of all levels may amount to 80.9 billion rubles.
During the year of operation of production in the Varna region, 346.3 million rubles were transferred to the budgets of different levels.
And this is for the first year.
&quot;The longer the company successfully operates, the higher the amount of deductions can be,&quot; Valery Ulanovsky added.
RMK clarified that in 2015 tax deductions from Mikheevsky GOK approached 1 billion rubles.
However, the participation of RCC enterprises in the life and development of the territories where they operate is not limited to tax deductions.
RCC enterprises help repair and maintain schools, kindergartens, sports facilities, build cultural and entertainment facilities, and improve territories.
In 2016, one of the largest social projects of the Russian Copper Company in Karabash was the overhaul, and in fact, the almost complete restructuring of Kindergarten N9 for 95 pupils.
The building, built in 1960, was in disrepair.
Also on the territory of the RMK Arena there will be a landscape park with an artificial pond, underground and above-ground parking lots for 600 cars, cafes and sports shops.
The RMK Arena will make it possible to hold spectacular professional sporting events of international level.
But the main task of this project is to make physical education and sports in comfortable conditions accessible to the residents of Chelyabinsk, especially for children.
