The military of the Black Sea Fleet conducted a practice of anti-submarine and sabotage defense in the Black Sea.
This was reported to RIA Novosti by the representative of the press service of the Ministry of Defense for the Navy Igor Dygalo.
The exercises were conducted as part of the first stage of exercises on special types of support for the actions of the Navy forces.
&quot;The servicemen of the anti-submarine and sabotage units worked out the anti-submarine and sabotage defense of the base of the fleet forces on the coast and the adjacent sea area of the Black Sea,&quot; Dygalo said.
The exercises involved about 400 servicemen, more than 10 units of military equipment, including Mi-8 and Ka-27 helicopters, Grachonok anti-sabotage boats and Raptor high-speed patrol boats.
In the course of the maneuvers, the forces of the patrol ships, using hydroacoustic means, discovered conditional sabotage groups and repulsed the attack of &quot;underwater saboteurs&quot; from the sea on the base of the Black Sea Fleet forces.
An air assault group landed from a Ka-27 helicopter, which blocked and destroyed the saboteurs of the mock enemy.
After that, minesweepers of the Black Sea Fleet went to sea to search for mines.
Dygalo said that &quot;these exercises of the Black Sea Fleet are being carried out in accordance with the plan for the preparation and conduct of the upcoming Kavkaz-2016 command and staff exercise and the Navy&#39;s training plan.&quot;
From July 18 to July 30, Ukraine and the United States held joint naval exercises Sea Breeze 2016 in the Black Sea.
In total, about four thousand people from 16 countries took part in the maneuvers.
More than 25 ships, boats and support vessels from the United States, Turkey, Romania and Ukraine were involved in the maritime component.
A court in the suburbs arrested the father for the murder of his adopted daughter Russian news EN
The Ozersky City Court of the Moscow Region authorized the arrest of Roman Chernikov, who confessed to the murder of his six-year-old adopted daughter.
