In particular, Roman Chernikov said that he committed the murder of a child on one of the days of April 2016 out of personal hostile relations, being at home in a state of alcoholic intoxication.
Then, in order to hide the body of the child, he burned it and scattered the remains along with his wife over a large area.
On the evening of August 9, during interrogation by the investigator, the adoptive parents reported that in April 2016, a six-year-old child drowned in a bathtub.
For a long time they managed to hide the disappearance of the girl from everyone, but in August, having learned that guardianship officers would soon come to their home, they decided to tell everyone that the child was missing.
The parents stated that on August 6, their adopted daughter arbitrarily left the territory of the plot of the house where they lived as a family and disappeared.
