Owners of instant messengers and mail services must identify users and delete prohibited information - this is the summary of the bill developed by the Media Communications Union (ISS), which unites the largest Russian telecom operators (Vedomosti has it).
Employees of three companies - members of the union confirmed that such a project is being discussed.
In early autumn, it should be presented to a working group led by First Deputy Prime Minister Igor Shuvalov, says Vedomosti&#39;s interlocutor in the ISS.
We are talking about amendments to the laws on communications and the media.
They stipulate that any &quot;organizer of the dissemination of information on the Internet, providing the possibility of exchanging electronic messages&quot; is obliged to identify users based on the information contained in the databases of telecom operators, having previously concluded contracts with them.
And also &quot;immediately block messages or publications that contain information disseminated in violation of the requirements of Russian law.&quot;
Otherwise, operators have the right to restrict access to the service by decision of Roskomnadzor.
