Sandwiched between Angola and South Africa, Namibia suffered greatly during the long struggle against apartheid.
However, since gaining independence from South Africa in 1990, this country of 2.4 million has made tremendous strides, especially in the last few years.
The main reason for Namibia&#39;s success is that the government places a lot of emphasis on education.
While people in developed countries take for granted free primary and secondary education, in many poor countries secondary and even primary schools require tuition fees.
Moreover, governments are often advised to introduce &quot;cost recovery&quot; tuition fees.
However, in Namibia, education in primary schools is free.
