Dongfeng will bring Fengguang 370 crossover and Rich New pickup truck to Russia - website Driving www.zr.ru
Dongfeng Fengguang 370 is a representative of a class of cars that is gaining popularity in China, combining the advantages of a minivan and a crossover.
Another announced Russian premiere is the Rich New pickup truck.
Many Western firms decided to ignore the Moscow International Motor Show this year, so Chinese firms will fill the emptiness of Crocus Expo showrooms.
In particular, Dongfeng Motor Corporation, which has great views on the Russian market and intends to offer our motorists a number of interesting new products in the near future, will act as a powerful front.
One of them will be the Dongfeng Fengguang 370 crossover, which went on sale in China this spring at a price of 55,900 yuan (just under 550,000 rubles at the current exchange rate).
The Russians are unlikely to get such a price tag, and the issue of deliveries to our country is still under discussion.
In China, by the way, following the results of June sales, the Fengguang 370 managed to reach 11th place in the list of the best-selling minivans, although due to the high ground clearance (175 mm) and the protective plastic body kit along the lower perimeter of the body, it can be considered a crossover.
Crossvan is built on the front-wheel drive platform of the younger model Fengguang 360, the 370 has the same wheelbase of 2725 mm, but the body is slightly longer (4565 mm versus 4510 mm), the design is more solid, and the equipment is richer.
The salon is decorated with wooden planks, but the large vertical touch screen &quot;like Tesla&quot; on the center console shown in the photo was only on the early exhibition copies of the crossvan, and cars with simpler &quot;music&quot; went on sale.
Five of the seven seats can be easily folded to form a flat loading area 1650 mm long, with a maximum trunk volume of 1500 liters.
The engine for the Fengguang 370 is only one - a 1.5-liter gasoline &quot;aspirated&quot; with a capacity of 115 hp, docked with a 5-speed manual gearbox.
The manufacturer is modestly silent about the dynamic qualities of the car, but promises a budget-friendly appetite of the owner at the level of 6.7 l / 100 km.
The Rich New pickup truck is the Nissan NP300 Navara of the generation before last, well known to Russians, but with a design slightly ennobled by Chinese stylists.
Despite the obsolete design, this model is still in stable demand among the Chinese consumer as a reliable and unpretentious workhorse.
At a reasonable price, Rich New will certainly interest Russians, too, because modern Japanese pickups have become prohibitively expensive.
Rich New is equipped with two engines to choose from: a 2.4 liter petrol (137 hp) or a 2.5 liter turbodiesel (116 hp).
Gearbox - only mechanics, drive - to the rear wheels, but there are modifications with a hard-wired front end.
The new flagship sedan A9 will also be at the Dongfeng booth, its Russian premiere was announced by the representative office of the Chinese company back in June.
There are more and more minivan-like crossovers in the Chinese market, one of the latest innovations is Cowin V3 and SWM X7.
Currently, the Russian Dongfeng line consists of two models: the S30 sedan and the H30 Cross hatchback.
For seven months of this year, the dealers of the Chinese company sold 696 cars in our country.
Notifications for transport tax will no longer be sent by mail - the site Behind the wheel www.zr.ru
The Tax Inspectorate has changed the procedure for sending property tax notices.
All Russian car owners are accustomed to the scheme that has not changed over the years: in summer and autumn they receive by mail receipts for paying transport tax for the previous year.
However, this year, many of them will not wait.
The fact is that the tax inspectorate quietly changed the procedure for notifying citizens.
Those who are registered in the &quot;Personal Account of the Taxpayer&quot; on the official website of the department nalog.ru will receive notifications in electronic form.
The inspection automatically considered such Russians as online users and deleted them from the standard, &quot;paper&quot; mailing list.
The innovation will affect all owners of vehicles and real estate.
Everyone else will continue to receive the usual emails.
However, the owners of an account on the site also have the opportunity to return to the old scheme.
To do this, they will have to visit the tax office during August and write an application.
On the one hand, the new order is more modern and more convenient.
The notification will appear in the &quot;personal account&quot; immediately after the compilation, while the letter will take several days and may be completely lost.
In addition, the number of users of the Internet service of the tax inspectorate has exceeded 18 million people, which will allow the department to seriously save on mailing lists.
On the other hand, modest news on the site of the inspection is clearly not enough to inform citizens about the changed order.
Some could register in the &quot;personal account&quot; for a one-time service and have long forgotten about it.
These people will not wait for notifications by mail and, without knowing it, will fall into the category of non-payers with all the ensuing consequences.
Access to the &quot;Taxpayer&#39;s Personal Account&quot; is carried out in three ways: through the gosuslugi.ru portal account, using an electronic signature or entering the login and password specified in the registration card.
The latter can be obtained in person at any branch of the tax office (regardless of the place of registration).
We remind you that this year the transport tax must be paid before December 1st.
The distribution of notifications began in July.
